description:
## Design Reference
@docs/design/recipe-new-session-toggle.md#code-examples

## Context
Adds the visual toggle to RecipeMenuView that allows users to enable/disable the "start in new session" behavior. The toggle appears as a Section at the top of the recipe list.

## Requirements
- [ ] Add Section with Toggle at top of List
- [ ] Toggle label: "Start in new session"
- [ ] Section footer explains behavior: "Creates a fresh session for this recipe instead of using the current session."
- [ ] Wrap existing recipe ForEach in a Section titled "Recipes"

## Technical Approach
- Files to modify: `ios/VoiceCode/Views/RecipeMenuView.swift`
- New files to create: None
- Dependencies: Task "Add state properties for new session toggle"

Replace the existing List content:
```swift
List {
    // NEW: Toggle section at top
    Section {
        Toggle("Start in new session", isOn: $useNewSession)
    } footer: {
        Text("Creates a fresh session for this recipe instead of using the current session.")
    }

    // Existing recipe list wrapped in section
    Section("Recipes") {
        ForEach(client.availableRecipes) { recipe in
            // ... existing RecipeRowView code ...
        }
    }
}
```

## Verification
- [ ] Build succeeds
- [ ] Toggle visible at top of recipe list when recipes are loaded
- [ ] Toggle can be switched ON/OFF
- [ ] Footer text displays correctly

## Acceptance Criteria
- Toggle labeled "Start in new session" appears in RecipeMenuView above the recipe list (AC #1)

## Parallelization
Can be worked alongside: None (depends on state properties task)
